title nasim — SBX-04 LIMIT Resources

' Participants with box colors per C4 layer

note over participants
  Scope:          Resource quota enforcement via cgroups
  Preconditions:  Sandbox instance created, limits defined
  Excludes:       Process monitoring (SBX-03)
  Contexts:       Called by SandboxExecutor during sandbox creation
  Rollback:       Remove cgroup on setup failure
  Design:         Linux cgroup v2 with CPU, memory, disk I/O limits
end note

== SBX-04 LIMIT Resources ==

SandboxExecutor -> ResourceLimiter: set_limits(cgroup_id, quotas)
ResourceLimiter -> ResourceLimiter: create cgroup v2 hierarchy
ResourceLimiter -> ResourceLimiter: set cpu.max (CPU quota)
ResourceLimiter -> ResourceLimiter: set memory.max (memory limit)
ResourceLimiter -> ResourceLimiter: set io.max (disk I/O limit)
ResourceLimiter --> SandboxExecutor: limits_applied(cgroup_id)

note over participants
  Flow:    Create cgroup -> set CPU -> set memory -> set I/O -> confirm
  State:   creating -> configuring -> applied
  Failure: Cgroup setup fails -> remove partial cgroup, return error
  Success: Executor receives cgroup with enforced limits
end note

@enduml